### 5. Eager Test — `OrderProcessor_FullWorkflow_Succeeds` (lines 57–63)

```csharp
processor.ValidateOrder(order);
processor.CalculateTotal(order);
processor.ApplyDiscount(order, "SAVE10");
processor.ReserveInventory(order);
processor.ProcessPayment(order, new CreditCard("4111111111111111"));
processor.SendConfirmation(order);
processor.UpdateOrderHistory(order);
```

**Risk:** 7 distinct production methods in one test. If it fails, you can't tell which step broke. Each method should be tested in isolation; if you need a workflow test, clearly mark it as an integration test.

**Fix:** Test each method individually, or if this is intentionally an integration test, rename and annotate it:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("Integration")]
public void FullOrderWorkflow_EndToEnd_Succeeds() { ... }
```

