## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Fix | Why first |
|----------|-------|-----|-----------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | Add assertions | Test is giving false confidence right now |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | Split into two tests | Hidden gap — one branch is untested |
| 3 | Mystery Guest | Inline test data | Test is broken on every machine except the author's |
| 4 | Sleepy Test | `await` instead of `Sleep` | Flaky + adds 2s to every run |
| 5 | Exception Handling | Use `Assert.ThrowsException` | Quick one-line refactor, safer |
| 6 | Eager Test | Split or label as integration | Clarifies intent, improves diagnosis |
| 7 | Sensitive Equality | Assert on properties | Prevents future false failures |
| 8 | Magic Numbers | Named constants | Improves readability |
| 9 | Assertion Roulette | Add messages | Better failure diagnostics |
| 10 | General Fixture | Remove `_logger` | Trivial cleanup |

Items 1–4 address tests that can silently pass while hiding real bugs or failing nondeterministically. Start there.
